Author: Vermalen
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: Week 17‚Äì23rd of September short overview and next week plans  https://medium.ip.sx/week-17-23rd-of-september-short-overview-and-next-week-plans-e1ed8abdb5c8    1. Product development  The last week was focused on final tuning of IPSX platform. The first IP exchange is almost ready to be launched! Its major components are: IP Marketplace, Provider Dashboard (including Package builder functionality), Requester Dashboard, IP Gateway, Hot Wallet (with deposit and withdrawal functionalities), Settings and Profile Menus. ‚Ä¢Don‚Äôt forget, you can always check code updates in the public GitHub repository here.  2. Marketing/Community ‚Ä¢As you noticed by now, the ‚ÄúIP Dictionary‚Äù series is receiving upgrades with a series of infographics. Head out to our blog and give a quick look to pill #1, pill #2 and pill #3. ‚Ä¢IPSX on DefCamp!! Our partners from DefCamp will organise their 9th edition of the Hacking & Information Security event during 8th-9th November 2018. That‚Äôs not all, during the event we will host blockchain hacking competitions. See you at DefCamp #9, registration details and more can me checked here! ‚Ä¢The enrollment in the Staking Program #2 is ongoing and will last until 1st of October. The Staking Program will be active over a period of 3 months, until the 1st of January 2019. Details can be found here. ‚Ä¢In the meantime, the other two programs are still open:  Testing Program Enrollment: info regarding the testing of the iOS app are detailed here. Extra tokens can be earned by reporting bugs and improvement suggestions. All issues should be reported here following the guidelines.  Referral Program: bringing new users to the IPSX platform can earn you extra tokens. For each referred individual that successfully registers through your referral link you will be rewarded 25 IPSX Tokens.  Next week plans ‚Ä¢Code freeze stage is about to come in short time and the last preparations for launching are to be made in the next days. Also, we will be running security audits amongst other things. ‚Ä¢Aaaaand stay tuned, updates for new features‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääwhich will be implemented after the first version of the platform‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääwill be disclosed these days!  As always, feel free to engage with our team, send us feedback, ask us questions and report anything you like or dislike about IPSX. We are here to answer to all of you.

Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: Week 3rd‚Äì9th of September short overview and next week plans  https://medium.ip.sx/week-3rd-9th-of-september-short-overview-and-next-week-plans-5a22dccdfca5  1. Product development ‚Ä¢Following the plan, last week we were working on additional features for the Marketplace component and furthermore, we are developing the API for iOS app. ‚Ä¢Also, as planned, we went on integrating the Marketplace component with Proxy Offers created through the Provider Dashboard. ‚Ä¢The specs for the first version of invoicing logic (Corporate & Retail users) has been drafted and is now pending implementation the Marketplace Database. ‚Ä¢Don‚Äôt forget, you can always check code updates in the public GitHub repository here.  2. Marketing/Community ‚Ä¢Testing Program Enrollment is still open. All info regarding the testing of the iOS app are detailed here. Extra tokens can be earned by reporting bugs and improvement suggestions. All issues should be reported here following the guidelines. ‚Ä¢Referral Program is still open. Bringing new users to the IPSX platform can earn you extra tokens. For each referred individual that successfully registers through your referral link you will be rewarded 25 IPSX Tokens. ‚Ä¢The first Staking Program was ended and the rewards were delivered to all the stakers. ‚Ä¢We are happy to announce our new team member, Andrei Petrache, Community Moderator. He is a cybernetics student with customer support skills, tech & esports enthusiast.  Next week plans ‚Ä¢We will advance with IPSX tokens Deposit and Withdrawal, flows through the Payment Gateway via API endpoints. ‚Ä¢The development of Webapp will be focused on the Marketplace & Provider Dashboard.

Author: LRPchange
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: The connections are logged to protect the actors in case someone does illegal activities with a rented IP. There will be a privacy mode for both providers and requesters, meaning that neither one of them will be able to see the traffic done by the other. We will address all these aspects in a detailed way soon, when we will release the technical documentation

Author: chayantoon
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: In the interest of protecting our customers and as a precautionary measure, we are temporarily suspending trading and deposits of all erc20 tokens along with a suspension of all withdrawals (fiat and crypto) across QRYPTOS and QUOINEX. We are doing this in response to the discovery of the BatchOverFlow smart contract bug, which can be exploited by an attacker to create an unlimited supply of erc20 tokens. We will resume normal business after we are certain there are no potential risks.‚Äù

Author: Vladdirescu87
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: IPSX Launches Demo, Secures Exchange Listings on Qryptos and Bibox, and Announces New Partnerships  IP address marketplace based on the blockchain, IPSX, has set a trailblazing pattern for success, achieving significant milestones in record time, quickly establishing itself as one of the most outstanding projects to emerge in the alternative cryptocurrency market.  Following its successful token generation event in early March that saw the Swiss-based tech firm raise over $8 million, IPSX is well on its way toward making its native IPSX token accessible and available to cryptocurrency users and traders across the globe.  It is now freely available to buy, sell and exchange on Quoine‚Äôs digital cryptocurrency exchange and trading platform, Qryptos Exchange. As the first international exchange to receive an official license by Japan‚Äôs Financial Services Agency, Qryptos has made a name for itself as a leading fintech provider of blockchain related trading, exchange and modern financial services.  Read the details in the article of Coinidol dot com, the world blockchain news outlet: https://coinidol.com/ipsx-announces-new-partnerships/

Author: ajieafianto
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: IP addresses you‚Äôre talking about (dynamic ones) are not constantly changing, you‚Äôre just getting a new one for each networking session (instead of having a constant one, static). For eg, for a cellular network you get a new IP each time you turn on and off airplane mode (hence, reconnect to the network).

Author: tientien333

The query will be something like: how often does dynamic IP address change (or just ask your internet provider). For cable though (Ethernet, without router) you can be getting new IP each time you restart you PC.

Author: S3cco
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: Bitcoin Garden: Meet IPSX ‚Äì An Advanced Platform for IP Sharing https://bitcoingarden.org/meet-ipsx-an-advanced-platform-for-ip-sharing/  IPSX is one of the first IP exchanges that connects different actors in a network involving the connection of peers. It enables the owners of the data centers and individuals to rent their IP addresses to other users. The users that rent out their IP address are known as ‚ÄúProviders‚Äù while those that rent the IP address are known as ‚ÄúRequesters‚Äù.  These IP addresses are used majorly to complete tasks that require more than one IP address, if not one, from different locations. IPSX stands for IP Sharing Exchange; where IP means Internet Protocol. IPSX has been showing a great prospect and might become one of the core components of the next layer of the web alongside distributed storage and processing tools. This layer is known as the distributed network layer.  IP addresses are a valuable asset today, and they have a very low liquidity level. Meaning that there is no simple solution to renting IP addresses using a specific list of filters. The resources for the IP are supplied by centralized providers that are controlled by closed networks, payment systems that are proprietary, and many other restrictions....

Author: piggyfrog
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: IPSX connects actors in a peer-to-peer network, enabling both data center owners and individual users, that will be called "providers" to rent IPs to other users, that will be called "requesters". The IPs can be used to complete different tasks requiring one or more IPs from different locations. Today, IP addresses are valuable assets with a low liquidity level due to the fact that there is not a simple solution to share/rent IPs based on a specific list of filters and IP resources are supplied by centralized providers which are constrained by closed networks, proprietary payment systems, and many other restrictions.   IPSX core built-in feature set is a dedicated Ethereum-based transaction system, which enables direct payments between requestors and providers solving all the above mentioned problems, increasing the liquidity of the IPs and allowing any actor that has an IP on his device that is connected to the internet to take part into a multi-billion yearly business, that otherwise is closed to home internet users.

Author: paskal_navi
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: Well, VPNs use this technology currently, so its nothing new from that perspective. The difference is instead of renting IP addresses from a business you can rent them from an individual VPN provider, Data Mining, software, web crawling bots etc all use bulk IP addresses. Please take a look, you will find it interesting: https://news4c.com/ipsx-brings-benefits-to-data-acquisition-for-big-data-analysis-and-scalability-solutions-targeted-at-vpn-providers/  Also, we have received many questions regarding the use cases of IPs. So we decided to come forth and meet your question in our latest blog post. Why are they useful (or even necessary in some cases), why would anyone share their IP? Or maybe you have liability concerns about what happens with your IPs. Read all about it in our latest blog post as we are shining some light upon the market and usage of IPs. https://medium.ip.sx/ipsx-use-cases-data-acquisition-for-big-data-analysis-and-scalability-solution-for-vpn-providers-10d7fb8c7dab

Author: MikeAngel
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: If someone sells his ip, will he have access to all clients traffic? how will this work?

Author: oni365
Title: [ANN]IPSX - IP Exchange, the Distributed Network Layer
Body: This is a very good question. There will be two types of traffic: standard mode - where the traffic will be visible, but the content will not be visible due to the client-server encryption. What that means: it will be visible that Gmail was accessed but the account used, passwords or any other data will not be accessible (basically all the content that an IPS can see will be visible). On the privacy mode, there will be nothing visible. We will release technical documentation and diagrams where we will explain how privacy mode works
